    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3787" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρμα</span></b>  (2), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ατος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">prop;</span> pl., of the
          supports placed under ships when drawn up on shore, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.486</span></i>; met., of persons, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρμα πόληος</span>, ‘prop and stay,’ ‘pillar’ of the
          state, <i><span class="en">Il. 16.549</span></i>; of an arrow,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μελαινέων ἕρμ̓ ὀδυνά̄ων</span>, ‘bearer of
          black pains,’ by some referred to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρμα
            1</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.117</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
